-- Monte Paschi has paid back 5 bln euros of ECB funds so far-source
-- By Silvia Aloisi and Stefano Bernabei
-- Tue Apr 29, 2014 06:17AM EDT
-- None



SIENA, Italy, April 29 (Reuters) - Italy's third biggest lender Monte dei Paschi di Siena <BMPS.MI> has so far paid back 5 billion euros ($6.92 billion) of cheap funds it borrowed from the European Central Bank, a source close to the bank told Reuters on Tuesday.

